# Security Best Practices

## 🔐 Key Management

### CRITICAL: NEVER commit private keys or .env files to version control!

### Hardhat
- **Always use .env files** (never commit!)
- Store private keys securely in password manager
- Use hardware wallets (Ledger/Trezor) for mainnet deployments
- Consider using AWS KMS or similar for production

### Foundry (RECOMMENDED for Production)
- **Use encrypted keystores** (most secure):
  ```bash
  # Import key with encryption
  cast wallet import mykey --interactive
  
  # Deploy using keystore (no private key in .env!)
  forge script Deploy.s.sol --account mykey --sender 0xYourAddress --broadcast
  ```
- Never use raw PRIVATE_KEY in .env for mainnet
- Store keystore files securely (they're encrypted but still sensitive)

### Mina Protocol
- Store keys in secure location with 700 permissions
- Use separate keys for testnet and mainnet
- Back up keys securely (encrypted storage)

## 📋 Pre-Deployment Checklist

Before deploying to ANY network:

- [ ] Code reviewed and audited (for mainnet)
- [ ] All tests passing
- [ ] Deployed and tested on testnet first
- [ ] Constructor arguments verified
- [ ] Gas limits checked
- [ ] Network configuration confirmed
- [ ] Deployment wallet funded
- [ ] Backup of deployment info prepared
- [ ] Block explorer verification plan ready

## 🚨 If Private Keys Are Compromised

**IMMEDIATE ACTIONS:**

1. **STOP all operations immediately**
2. **Transfer all funds** to new secure address
3. **Revoke all permissions** and approvals
4. **Generate new keys** using secure method
5. **Document the incident** (time, scope, actions taken)
6. **Review access logs** if available
7. **Notify team/stakeholders** if applicable
8. **Post-mortem**: Determine how compromise occurred

## 🛡️ Additional Security Measures

### Contract Security
- Use OpenZeppelin contracts when possible
- Implement access control (Ownable, AccessControl)
- Add pause functionality for emergencies
- Use ReentrancyGuard for external calls
- Validate all inputs
- Follow checks-effects-interactions pattern

### Deployment Security
- Deploy from dedicated deployment address
- Use multi-sig for contract ownership (mainnet)
- Implement timelock for critical functions
- Set up monitoring and alerts
- Have emergency response plan

### Operational Security
- Use separate machines for mainnet operations
- Keep systems updated and patched
- Use 2FA everywhere possible
- Limit access to production keys
- Regular security audits
- Incident response procedures documented

## 📱 Monitoring

Set up monitoring for:
- Unexpected transactions
- Balance changes
- Contract interactions
- Gas price anomalies
- Failed transactions

## 🔄 Key Rotation

- Rotate deployment keys periodically
- Use different keys for different networks
- Maintain key inventory
- Document key purposes and locations (securely)

## ⚖️ Compliance

- Understand regulatory requirements for your jurisdiction
- Maintain audit trails
- Document all deployments
- Keep records of all transactions

## 📚 Resources

- OpenZeppelin Security: https://docs.openzeppelin.com/contracts/security
- Ethereum Smart Contract Best Practices: https://consensys.github.io/smart-contract-best-practices/
- Foundry Security: https://book.getfoundry.sh/tutorials/best-practices
- Mina Protocol Security: https://docs.minaprotocol.com/zkapps/writing-a-zkapp/introduction-to-zkapps/secure-zkapps
